description.p:
Accordingly, the present invention provides a phage display system for displaying a polypeptide on the outer surface of a phage, comprising:

(a) a phagemid comprising a coding sequence that encodes the polypeptide fused in-frame to a first adapter sequence, wherein the phagemid is devoid of sequences encoding any phage coat proteins;
(b) a phage helper vector comprising sequences encoding all phage coat proteins necessary for packaging the phage, wherein at least one of the phage coat proteins is fused in-frame to a second adapter, said first and second adapter acting, when the polypeptide is produced in a suitable host cell, to cause the display of the polypeptide via binding between the first and second adapters to form a stable complex;

wherein the first and second adapters mediate dimerization via the formation of a coiled coil dimer.

claim.claim-text:
A phage display system for displaying a polypeptide on the outer surface of a phage, comprising:
(a) a phagemid comprising a coding sequence that encodes the polypeptide fused in-frame to a first adapter sequence, wherein the phagemid is devoid of sequences encoding any phage coat proteins;
(b) a phage helper vector comprising sequences encoding all phage coat proteins necessary for packaging the phage, wherein at least one of the phage coat proteins is fused in-frame to a second adapter, said first and second adapter acting, when the polypeptide is produced in a suitable host cell, to cause the display of the polypeptide via binding between the first and second adapters to form a stable complex;

wherein the first and second adapters mediate dimerization via the formation of a coiled coil dimer.

